vulnerability.name: USN-5959-1
vulnerability.description: It was discovered that Kerberos incorrectly handled memory when processing KDC data, which could lead to a NULL pointer dereference. An attacker could possibly use this issue to cause a denial of service or have other unspecified impacts. (CVE-2021-36222, CVE-2021-37750)

statements.status_notes: Several security issues were fixed in Kerberos.
